Hi,
On Mon, 31 May 1999 01:30:59 -0700, Lamar Williams <lamar@custom-sd.com>
said:
> How does one access a raw disk ?
> I see the block device name "/dev/hda?", what are the character device
> names ?
Go to 
ftp://ftp.uk.linux.org/pub/linux/sct/fs/raw-io/
 and pick up the
latest diffs.  Read the README, build a new kernel, set up /dev and
start running raw character devices.
--Stephen
